data.chText: 美发厅；美容厅；高级服装店
data.enText: a shop/store that gives customers hair or beauty treatment or that sells expensive clothes
a room in a large house used for entertaining guests

data.chText: 沙龙（旧时作家、艺术家等在名流家中定期举行的聚会）
data.enText: (in the past) a regular meeting of writers, artists and other guests at the house of a famous or important person

means: 沙龙(旧时作家、艺术家等在名流家中定期举行的聚会)

tr: elegant sitting room where guests are received
gallery where works of art can be displayed
a shop where hairdressers and beauticians work

value.def: A salon is a place where people have their hair cut or coloured, or have beauty treatments.
A salon is a shop where smart, expensive clothes are sold.
A salon is an informal meeting of fashionable writers or artists, which is held at the house of someone who is well-known. Salons were more common in former times.

example.ex: His apartment was the most famous literary salon in Russia.
example.tran: 他的公寓是俄国最著名的文学沙龙会所。

value.tran: (旧时较为流行的)文艺界名流聚会，雅集，文艺沙龙

value.def: A salon is a sitting room in a large, grand house.
